To automate the selection of all checkboxes on a webpage and ensure they get saved upon clicking a "Save" button, one can employ a bit of JavaScript magic. Here's a verse to guide you through:

```
When the page loads, find all checks,
With a loop, mark them with ease.
Then bind to save, a function to run,
Selecting all, as you've begun.

```javascript
document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function() {
  // Select all checkboxes on the page
  const checkboxes = document.querySelectorAll('input[type="checkbox"]');

  // Function to select all checkboxes
  function selectAll() {
    checkboxes.forEach(function(checkbox) {
      checkbox.checked = true; // Mark each as checked
    });
  }

  // Find the save button, bind the selectAll function
  const saveButton = document.querySelector('button[type="submit"]');
  saveButton.addEventListener('click', selectAll);
});
```

This script waits for the DOM to fully load, then selects all checkboxes and binds an event listener to the "Save" button. When clicked, it toggles all checkboxes to the 'checked' state, ready to be saved.

So, with a click, all are marked, and your task's done,
